read it because...

778
00:45:12.501 --> 00:45:14.253
it's starting to make sense to me...

779
00:45:15.379 --> 00:45:16.756
why she did what she did.

780
00:45:18.799 --> 00:45:20.176
I can help you through this.

781
00:45:20.843 --> 00:45:22.428
Can you tell me why I'm on the tapes?

782
00:45:23.679 --> 00:45:26.098
You have to listen.
It's what Hannah wanted.

783
00:45:26.182 --> 00:45:28.059
Yeah. yeah. I know.
What Hannah wanted.

784
00:45:28.476 --> 00:45:30.478
What you're so sure of.
but you won't say how.

785
00:45:34.273 --> 00:45:35.274
Huh?

786
00:45:39.695 --> 00:45:40.696
Fine.

787
00:45:40.780 --> 00:45:41.822
Forget you. then.

788
00:45:42.156 --> 00:45:43.491
Let me help you.

789
00:45:44.617 --> 00:45:46.869
What. like you've been
helping me so far?

790
00:45:47.119 --> 00:45:48.329
No. thanks.

791
00:45:49.664 --> 00:45:50.957
But look on the bright side...

792
00:45:51.791 --> 00:45:53.167
you don't have to follow me anymore.

793
00:45:55.670 --> 00:45:58.422
HANNAH: <i>No one knows what's really
going on in another person's life.</i>

794
00:45:59.715 --> 00:46:02.885
<i>And you never know how what you do
will affect someone else.</i>

795
00:46:03.010 --> 00:46:04.303
Hey. Bryce. what's up?

796
00:46:04.762 --> 00:46:06.097
Hey. Jensen.

797
00:46:07.932 --> 00:46:09.183
<i>And if that goes for me.</i>

798
00:46:09.475 --> 00:46:10.977
<i>it must go for everyone.</i>

799
00:46:13.437 --> 00:46:14.605
<i>Even cheerleaders.</i>

800
00:46:15.481 --> 00:46:16.774
CLAY: Hey. Sheri.

801
00:46:16.941 --> 00:46:18.442
How was the rest of your weekend?

802
00:46:18.859 --> 00:46:19.860
Sorry. what?

803
00:46:19.944 --> 00:46:21.153
You were great at the game.

804
00:46:26.784 --> 00:46:28.536
Jessica. Hey. how are you?

805
00:46:29.870 --> 00:46:30.871
Hey. Clay.

806
00:46:32.498 --> 00:46:34.667
Hey. Justin. good game the other night.

807
00:46:40.923 --> 00:46:42.133
What the fuck is going on?

808
00:46:42.466 --> 00:46:43.634
Who knows anymore?

809
00:46:45.803 --> 00:46:47.179
(P.A. SCREECHES)

810
00:46:47.513 --> 00:46:49.515
STUDANT ON P.A.:
<i>Can I have your attention. please?</i>

811
00:46:50.599 --> 00:46:52.518
HANNAH'S RECORDING OVER P.A.:
<i>Hey. it's Hannah.</i>

812
00:46:53.602 --> 00:46:54.812
<i>Hannah Baker.</i>

813
00:46:56.313 --> 00:46:57.690
<i>That's right.</i>

814
00:46:58.024 --> 00:47:01.068
<i>Don't adjust your...
whatever device you're hearing this on.</i>

815
00:47:01.986 --> 00:47:02.820
<i>It's me.</i>

816
00:47:03.738 --> 00:47:05.364
<i>Live and in stereo.</i>

817
00:47:06.949 --> 00:47:08.492
<i>No return engagements.</i>

818
00:47:08.576 --> 00:47:09.702
<i>no encore...</i>

819
00:47:10.244 --> 00:47:13.497
STUDENT OVER P.A.: a<i> huge congrats</i>
<i>to our Tiger team for Saturday's win.</i>

820
00:47:13.581 --> 00:47:15.875
<i>A special shout-out to Zach Dempsey.</i>

821
00:47:15.958 --> 00:47:18.419
<i>who crushed it with 28 points.</i>

822
00:47:18.502 --> 00:47:19.962
<i>In other athletic news.</i>

823
00:47:20.046 --> 00:47:21.922
<i>the Lady Tigers won their game</i>

824
00:47:22.006 --> 00:47:24.091
<i>by a score of 54-32.</i>

825
00:47:27.303 --> 00:47:28.679
Thought you said this wasn't a test.

826
00:47:29.764 --> 00:47:31.349
'Cause this looks like a test.

827
00:47:31.515 --> 00:47:33.559
It's not. Mr. Pratters. I assure you.

828
00:47:33.642 --> 00:47:36.687
It is a character-building questionnaire
that assesses

829
00:47:36.771 --> 00:47:38.689
personal strengths and weaknesses.

830
00:47:58.250 --> 00:47:59.627
Excuse me. Mrs. Bradley?

831
00:47:59.794 --> 00:48:00.878
Yes. Clay.

832
00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:03.756
How important was it to you
to help Hannah Baker?

833
00:48:06.550 --> 00:48:09.261
Extremely important to me. Clay.
Why do you ask?

834
00:48:11.889 --> 00:48:14.225
Remember that note you got
in your bag last year?

835
00:48:15.893 --> 00:48:17.853
The one about
not feeling anything anymore?

836
00:48:22.274 --> 00:48:23.442
It was from Hannah.

837
00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:27.988
Okay. uh. why do you think that is?

838
00:48:28.072 --> 00:48:29.198
(DOOR OPENS)

839
00:48:30.407 --> 00:48:31.408
- Mrs. Bradley?
- Yes?

840
00:48:31.492 --> 00:48:33.577
Sorry to interrupt.
but I need Mr. Jensen.

841
00:48:34.203 --> 00:48:35.496
MRS. BRADLEY: Okay. Mr. Porter.

842
00:48:35.579 --> 00:48:38.165
Clay. we can continue this
discussion at another time.

843
00:48:40.126 --> 00:48:41.919
I have to say. I'm a little surprised.

844
00:48:42.837 --> 00:48:43.879
What? Why?

845
00:48:44.213 --> 00:48:45.422
I know it's been a few weeks.

846
00:48:45.506 --> 00:48:48.134
but you seem like the type of kid
to follow through on a promise.

847
00:48:49.260 --> 00:48:50.302
COURTNEY: Don't worry. Clay.

848
00:48:50.636 --> 00:48:52.304
I almost forgot too.

849
00:48:53.389 --> 00:48:54.473
Forgot what?

850
00:48:54.557 --> 00:48:57.309
Courtney and Clay. these are
our new foreign exchange students

851
00:48:57.393 --> 00:48:59.228
joining us this semester.

852
00:48:59.437 --> 00:49:03.732
This is Jhene. Fynn.
Mahla and Deep.

853
00:49:03.899 --> 00:49:06.527
Uh. Courtney and Clay
will be helping you out.

854
00:49:06.610 --> 00:49:09.405
They are on the Honor Board
and they'll be giving you the tour.

855
00:49:09.738 --> 00:49:11.031
The insider's tour!

856
00:49:11.282 --> 00:49:13.701
All the secrets that you need to know.

857
00:49:16.704 --> 00:49:17.997
Okay. great.

858
00:49:21.458 --> 00:49:22.543
CLAY: <i>So as you can see.</i>

859
00:49:22.626 --> 00:49:25.421
it's one of the finest high school
parking lots in the world.

860
00:49:25.921 --> 00:49:27.298
Oh. and right here is the library.

861
00:49:27.381 --> 00:49:31.051
where you can find books and tables
and chairs and all that stuff...

862
00:49:31.468 --> 00:49:32.720
state-of-the-art computers.

863
00:49:32.803 --> 00:49:34.805
at least if the art was ten years ago...

864
00:49:35.139 --> 00:49:36.265
and friendly librarians.

865
00:49:36.432 --> 00:49:39.268
Not super bright always. but friendly.

866
00:49:42.771 --> 00:49:44.315
Oh. wait. everyone.

867
00:49:44.565 --> 00:49:47.234
It's Justin Foley and Zach Dempsey.

868
00:49:47.318 --> 00:49:49.278
star basketball players
here at Liberty High.

869
00:49:49.361 --> 00:49:51.697
Hey. Justin. where's my bike?

870
00:49:52.114 --> 00:49:53.240
Justin stole my bike.

871
00:49:53.824 --> 00:49:55.284
What the fuck?
What are you doing?

872
00:49:55.367 --> 00:49:57.369
I'm giving our new
foreign exchange students a tour.

873
00:49:57.453 --> 00:49:59.830
Figured they should know
who owns the school. right. you guys?

874
00:49:59.914 --> 00:50:00.915
Clay.

875
00:50:01.040 --> 00:50:02.333
Right. right. Moving on.

876
00:50:02.458 --> 00:50:03.459
Where were we?

877
00:50:03.542 --> 00:50:04.543
Right. The auditorium.

878
00:50:04.627 --> 00:50:06.212
Oh. oh. but before we go...

879
00:50:07.004 --> 00:50:08.923
I want to show you something super cool.

880
00:50:09.465 --> 00:50:11.342
- Okay?
- Clay. cut it out.

881
00:50:12.051 --> 00:50:13.594
Look at these lockers.

882
00:50:14.178 --> 00:50:15.721
They all look alike. right?

883
00:50:17.765 --> 00:50:18.599
Not this one.

884
00:50:21.060 --> 00:50:22.228
This one is special.

885
00:50:23.145 --> 00:50:25.064
It belonged to a girl who killed herself.

886
00:50:25.272 --> 00:50:26.482
Clay. come on.

887
00:50:26.565 --> 00:50:29.485
You see all these "don't kill yourself"
posters up on the wall?

888
00:50:29.610 --> 00:50:30.861
They weren't up before.

889
00:50:30.945 --> 00:50:33.280
They put them up
<i>because </i>she killed herself.

890
00:50:33.405 --> 00:50:34.406
And why did she do it?

891
00:50:34.490 --> 00:50:36.283
Because the kids here
treated her like shit!

892
00:50:36.367 --> 00:50:37.618
JUSTIN: Jensen. that's enough.

893
00:50:37.743 --> 00:50:39.787
But no one wants to admit it.
so they paint over the bathrooms

894
00:50:39.870 --> 00:50:42.706
and put up a memorial. because that's
the kind of school that this is.

895
00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:45.417
Everyone is just so <i>nice</i>
until they drive you to kill yourself.

896
00:50:45.626 --> 00:50:47.586
And sooner or later.
the truth will come out.

897
00:50:49.630 --> 00:50:50.714
It's gonna come out.

898
00:50:55.302 --> 00:50:57.721
Right. Tony? Right? You know the truth.

899
00:50:58.138 --> 00:50:59.098
MR. PORTER: Clay.

900
00:51:00.849 --> 00:51:02.851
I think you should come with me right now.

901
00:51:04.186 --> 00:51:05.980
Get to class. everybody!

902
00:51:06.563 --> 00:51:08.148
All you. get to class.

903
00:51:11.443 --> 00:51:12.653
Welcome to Liberty High.

904
00:51:13.654 --> 00:51:14.655
Let's go.

905
00:51:24.456 --> 00:51:25.457
Okay.

906
00:51:26.750 --> 00:51:27.626
New game.

907
00:51:31.130 --> 00:51:32.881
("THE WALLS CAME DOWN" PLAYING)

908
00:52:02.995 --> 00:52:04.496
<i>♪ Well they blew the horns ♪</i>

909
00:52:06.582 --> 00:52:08.042
<i>♪ And the walls came down ♪</i>

910
00:52:10.336 --> 00:52:11.628
<i>♪ They'd all been warned ♪</i>

911
00:52:13.839 --> 00:52:15.341
<i>♪ And the walls came down ♪</i>

912
00:52:17.801 --> 00:52:19.345
<i>♪ They stood there laughing </i>♪

913
00:52:21.096 --> 00:52:22.806
<i>♪ They're not laughing anymore ♪</i>

914
00:52:25.142 --> 00:52:26.518
<i>♪ The walls came down ♪</i>

915
00:52:32.524 --> 00:52:34.026
<i>♪ Sanctuary fades ♪</i>

916
00:52:36.070 --> 00:52:37.529
<i>♪ Congregation splits ♪</i>

917
00:52:39.531 --> 00:52:41.450
<i>♪ Nightly military raids ♪</i>

918
00:52:43.243 --> 00:52:44.953
<i>♪ The congregation splits ♪</i>

919
00:52:46.872 --> 00:52:48.832
<i>♪ It's a song of assassins ♪</i>

920
00:52:50.584 --> 00:52:52.378
<i>♪ Ringin' in your ears ♪</i>

921
